 Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Renoul","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French and Channel Islands: from a Norman French personal name deriving from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Raginwulf</i>, composed of the elements <i>ragin</i> ‘counsel, decision’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’."],"variants":[{"name":"Renew","meanings":["from the Late Latin name <i>Renata</i>, feminine of <i>Renatus</i> ‘reborn’, used by early Christians as a baptismal name celebrating spiritual rebirth in Christ. The name is also used in the English-speaking world, often without the accent and in a highly Anglicized pronunciation (  compare  Reenie  )."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Profit’ or ‘sharp’.","2  ♀, ♂ ‘Upright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Renoul II de Culant was born in 1185, in Tournon, Ardèche, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France as the son of Hélie DE CULANT. He married Marguerite DE BLAISON MIREBEAU in 1209, in Tournon, Ardèche, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died after 1253."},"et":{"1185–AFT 1253":"1185–pärast 1253","1185–1253":"1185–1253","1185–1252":"1185–1252","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1150–1217":"1150–1217","1217":"1217","AFT 1253":"pärast 1253","about 1207":"umbes 1207","1210":"1210","1253":"1253","1252":"1252","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","1209":"1209","1270":"1270","1207":"1207","Guillant, Tournon-sur-Rhône, Ardeche, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Tournon, Ardèche, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","Bo